l who is ineligible under paragraph (b)(2) of this section; or (iii) Quits work, if the individual was employed in work which was not suitable (as defined in §617.22(a)(1)), and it was reasonable and necessary for the individual to quit work to begin or continue training approved for the individual under §617.22(a). (2) Trainees ineligible. (i) An individual who, without justifiable cause, fails to begin participation in a training program which is approved under §617.22(a), or ceases to participate in such training, or for whom a waiver is revoked pursuant to §617.19(c), shall not be eligible for basic TRA, or any other payment under this part 617, for the week in which such failure, cessation, or revocation occurred, or any succeeding week thereafter until the week in which the individual begins or resumes participation in a training program that is approved under §617.22(a).
